* [[Alabama Agricultural and Mechanical University|Alabama A&M Bulldogs]] ([[Division I (NCAA)|NCAA D-I/I-AA]], [[Southwestern Athletic Conference|SWAC]]) and [[University of Alabama in Huntsville|UAH Chargers]] ([[Division II (NCAA)|NCAA D-II]], [[Gulf South Conference|GSC]] & [[Alabama-Huntsville Chargers hockey|CHA]]) athletics
* Huntsville Rugby Club<ref>{{cite web|url=http://huntsvillerugby.com/ |title=Huntsville Rugby Club |publisher=Huntsvillerugby.com |date=2011-11-05 |accessdate=2011-11-09}}</ref> - USA Rugby South Div. II<ref>{{cite web|title=MidSouth Rugby|url=http://www.midsouthrugby.com/MidSouth/Home.html|accessdate=16 July 2011|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/60E4bMTZK|archivedate=16 July 2011|deadurl=no}}</ref>
* Oakwood College Ambassadors Men's College Basketball (USCAA Div. 1)
* [[Tennessee Valley Tigers]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tigersIWFL.com/ |title=Tennessee Valley Tigers |publisher=Tigersiwfl.com |date= |accessdate=2011-11-09}}</ref> - [[Independent Women's Football League]]
* [[Rocket City Titans]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rocketcitytitans.com |title=Premier South Football League |publisher=Rocketcitytitans.com |date= |accessdate=2011-11-09}}</ref> - 2010 Inaugural Semi Pro football season.  Part of the [[Premier South Football League]].<ref>http://www.thepsfl.org</ref>

===Past sports franchises===
*[[Alabama Hawks]] (1968<U+2013>69) ([[Continental Football League]])
*Huntsville Lasers (1991<U+2013>92) ([[Global Basketball Association]])
*[[Huntsville Blast]] (1993<U+2013>94) ([[East Coast Hockey League]])
*Huntsville Fire (1997<U+2013>98) ([[Eastern Indoor Soccer League]])
*[[Huntsville Channel Cats]]/[[Huntsville Tornado]] (1995<U+2013>2001, 2003<U+2013>04) ([[Southern Hockey League (1995<U+2013>1996)|Southern Hockey League]] 1995-96; [[Central Hockey League]] 1996<U+2013>2001; [[South East Hockey League]] 2003-04)
*[[Huntsville Flight]] (2001<U+2013>05) ([[NBA Development League]])
*[[Rock River Raptors|Tennessee Valley Raptors]] (2005) ([[United Indoor Football]] league)

